<div align=left class=normal>
<p>
  
<a href="/default.asp?action=print&dest=skills">view for print</a>
<p>
    <font class=display-side>Abjuration</font><br>
      One of the several skills related to the art of magic, abjuration deals 
      with defensive magic, for example a spell that enables the character to 
      take less damage from extreme cold.<p>
    <font class=display-side>Alchemy</font><br>
      Grants the ability for a few residents of Norrath to make benificial potions<p>
    <font class=display-side>Alcohol Tolerance</font><br>
      The ability to handle alcohol.{Glug glug}<p>
    <font class=display-side>Alteration</font><br>
      Another of the several skills related to the art of magic, alteration deals 
      with changing things, whether it be illusion or an actual physical change. 
      An example would be a spell that teleports something, or that enables a 
      character to move faster, or forces him or her to move more slowly. <p>
    <font class=display-side>Apply Poison</font><br>
      A rogue only skill, if successfull it applys poison to the weapon to last 
      for the duration of the zone.<p>
    <font class=display-side>Archery</font><br>
      Archery deals with a the ability in using bows.<p>
    <font class=display-side>Backstabbing</font><br>
      The Rogue has the ability to make an increased damage when attacking from 
      the back side.<p>
    <font class=display-side>Baking</font> <br>
      Ability to bake goods with the remains of monsters..<p>
    <font class=display-side>Beg</font> <br>
      Ability to beg money from NPC characters - Can get ya killed<p>
    <font class=display-side>Bind Wound</font><br>
      BW gives you the ability to Bandage your wounds or anothers persons up to 
      50%. Need bandages however. <p>
    <font class=display-side>Bash</font><br>
      Disrupts the spell caster's magic.<p>
    <font class=display-side>Block</font><br>
      The ability to block an blow so that it doesnt hit you.<p>
    <font class=display-side>Brass Instruments</font> <br>
      A unique skill to a Bard. Some of there spells can only be casted through 
      this instrument.<p>
    <font class=display-side>Brewing</font> <br>
      The art of Brewing lets you create some mighty fine alcohol bevarages.<p>
    <font class=display-side>Channeling</font><br>
      One of the several skills related to the art of magic, channeling allows 
      the caster to decrease the amount of time necessary to cast a spell, regardless 
      of its nature. <p>
    <font class=display-side>Common Tongue</font> <br>
      Ability to speak and understand the Common Tongue. <p>
    <font class=display-side>Conjuration</font><br>
      Another of the several skills related to the art of magic, conjuration brings 
      something from elsewhere into the world, whether they be elemental creatures 
      or powerful clouds of energy. <p>
    <font class=display-side>Dark Speech</font><br>
      Ability to understand the evil languages in Norrath, including the side 
      tongue of Dark Elf, Ogre, and Troll.<p>
    <font class=display-side>Defense</font><br>
      How to avoid getting damaged during combat.<p>
    <font class=display-side>Disarm</font><br>
      This skill allows the combatant to dislodge a wielded weapon from his opponents 
      hands, knocking it to the ground, and forcing him, at least for the moment, 
      to fight hand-to-hand.<p>
    <font class=display-side>Disarm Traps</font><br>
      One of the reasons why you always want a rogue in your party, to disarm 
      these traps!<p>
    <font class=display-side>Divination</font><br>
      Another of the several skills related to the art of magic, spells of divination 
      allow the caster to both detect things previously concealed, as well as 
      to conceal things previously visible. <p>
    <font class=display-side>Dodge</font><br>
      One of the better ways to negate damage is to completely avoid the blow 
      itself, and the skill of dodging allows the combatant to do just that. <p>
    <font class=display-side>Double Attack</font><br>
      Allows for a chance of getting another attack.<p>
    <font class=display-side>Dragon Punch</font><br>
      side Monk attack.<p>
    <font class=display-side>Dual Wield</font><br>
      Certain classes will be able to wield a weapon effectively in both hands, 
      thereby increasing the number of attacks and thus the amount of damage dealt 
      in a given amount of time. <p>
    <font class=display-side>Eagle Strike</font><br>
      side Monk attack. <p>
    <font class=display-side>Elder Elvish</font><br>
      Ability to speak and comprehend the language of Elder Elvish. <p>
    <font class=display-side>Evocation</font><br>
      Another of the several skills related to the art of magic, evocation deals 
      with things that go boom. Fireballs, force spells, etc. all fall under the 
      auspices of this offensive skill. <p>
    <font class=display-side>Feign Death</font> <br>
      If successful the monsters will believe that you have died.<p>
    <font class=display-side>Fishing</font> <br>
      Lets you fish for food and other odds and ends.<p>
    <font class=display-side>Fletching</font> <br>
      The ability to craft fine bows and arrows<p>
    <font class=display-side>Flying Kick</font><br>
      side Monk attack. <p>
    <font class=display-side>Foraging</font><br>
      The ability to search your suroundings for food and water.<p>
    <font class=display-side>Hand-to-Hand</font><br>
      This is the skill that makes Monks shine. <p>
    <font class=display-side>Hide</font> <br>
      The ability to camoflauge yourself to an area.<p>
    <font class=display-side>Instill Doubt</font>
      <br>
      This skill if successful causes the enemy to run away feared.<p>
    <font class=display-side>Jewel Craft</font> <br>
      Ability to make Rings and other assorted jewelry.<p>
    <font class=display-side>Kick</font><br>
      Just what it says This allows you to Kick your attacker.<p>
    <font class=display-side>Make Poison<br>
      </font>A skill unique to the Rogue class make poison!<p>
    <font class=display-side>Meditate</font><br>
      Another of the several skills related to the art of magic, meditation allows 
      the caster to memorize spells more quickly.<p>
    <font class=display-side>Mend Wounds</font> <br>
      Monks ability to heal their wounds 25% - this can fail and take the same 
      25% away and has been known to kill as well if below 25%.<p>
    <font class=display-side>Offense</font><br>
      The overall ability to inflict damage upon an enemy during combat. <p>
    <font class=display-side>Old Erudian</font><br>
      Ability to speak and comprehend Old Erudian. <p>
    <font class=display-side>One-Hand Blunt</font> <br>
      Ability to use a blunt object<p>
    <font class=display-side>One-Hand Slashing</font> <br>
      Ability to hit others with one-handed weapons, such as long swords and mino 
      axes. <p>
    <font class=display-side>Parry</font> <br>
      An ability to deflect blows from an enemy with your weapon.<p>
    <font class=display-side>Percussion</font> <br>
      The ability of the Bard to use the drums, a few of their songs can only 
      be played through this device.<p>
    <font class=display-side>Pick Lock</font><br>
      Rogue ability to get by without keys <p>
    <font class=display-side>Pick Pocket</font><br>
      Hmmm take something from another character. <p>
    <font class=display-side>Piercing</font> <br>
      Ability to use piercing weapons, such as spears and daggers. <p>
    <font class=display-side>Pottery</font> <br>
      You can make containers with this skill. <p>
    <font class=display-side>Research</font><br>
      Permits the magic using classes to assemble spells from component pieces. 
      Spell Research is a trade skill, similar in theory to tailoring and cooking. 
      Specific items are inserted in to a container, combining to produce a new 
      item.<p>
    <font class=display-side>Riposte</font> <br>
      side attack. <p>
    <font class=display-side>Round Kick</font> <br>
      side Monk attack. <p>
    <font class=display-side>Safe Fall</font><br>
      The ability to fall and take less or no damage . <p>
    <font class=display-side>Sense Direction</font><br>
      Very useful skill here this tells you what direction your facing. <p>
    <font class=display-side>Singing</font><br>
      This is a Bard skill used when singing their beautiful songs. <p>
    <font class=display-side>Slam <br>
      </font>An ability that allows an user to slam there oppenents. Usually preferred 
      by a larger class like a Barbarian, Troll or Ogre.<p>
    <font class=display-side>Smithing</font> <br>
      This lets you make certain armor in the game.<p>
    <font class=display-side>Sneak</font> <br>
      Ability to sneak up on other players and NPCs unnoticed, a skill commonly 
      used by a rogue. When used, walking pace is slowed to half of normal speed. 
      <p>
    <font class=display-side>sideization</font><br>
      When a magic user attains a high enough level (usually quite high) this 
      skill becomes available. It allows the user to "sideize" in the spellcasting 
      skill of his or her choice. The added talent in the selected area allows 
      the magic user to cast faster and with less mana usage.<p>
    <font class=display-side>Steal</font><br>
      Another art known only to the more shady of individuals, this Rogue-specific 
      skill allows the miscreant to pilfer items from both players and NPCs. Their 
      intended victim, however, will at times detect this activity, and will rarely 
      appreciate the attempt. <p>
    <font class=display-side>Stringed Instruments</font><br>
      Certain Bard songs require certain instruments, and the better the minstrel 
      is at playing Stringed Instruments, the more effective he or she will be 
      at playing those songs.<p>
    <font class=display-side>Swimming</font><br>
      This skill the higher it gets the faster you swim.<p>
    <font class=display-side>Taunt</font> <br>
      This attempts to bring the attackers focus upon you.<p>
    <font class=display-side>Throwing</font> <br>
      Ability to use throwing weapons, like throwing daggers.<p>
    <font class=display-side>Tiger Claw</font><br>
      side Monk attack. <p>
    <font class=display-side>Tinkering</font> <br>
      Allows Gnomes to make mechanical items.<p>
    <font class=display-side>Thieves Cant</font><br>
      Secret thieves' language performed by using body language.<p>
    <font class=display-side>Track</font> <br>
      Ability of the user to sense the presence of others in the area. <p>
    <font class=display-side>Two-Handed Blunt</font> <br>
      Ability to use two-handed blunt weapons, such as Great staffs.. <p>
    <font class=display-side>Two-Handed Slashing</font><br>
      Ability to use two-handed slashing weapons, including the awe inspiring 
      executioners axe.. <p>
    <font class=display-side>Wind Instruments</font><br>
      Certain Bard songs require certain instruments, and the better the minstrel 
      is at playing Wind Instruments, the more effective he or she will be at 
      playing those songs. <p>

